<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
Trap doors can drop you past a random quest.  This behavior is surprising given the lengths the developers have gone to prevent players from sneaking past nasty quests in Angband. <p>
<strong><a class="nonexistent" href="./XandorTikroth">XandorTikroth</a></strong>: Well, I have seen something like this on the ToME Forums, and I can't rightly decern whether it's a bug or a feature.  If it were a bug, wouldn't that mean disabling those traps (or removing them from the game entirely) for certain levels?  I'm not very experienced with coding, but my instinct tells me that it would be pretty nasty trying to pull that off... 
</p>
<p>
And what about the monsters that do the following: 
</p>
<p>
Foo points at your feet You sink through the floor A Princess yells... 
</p>
<p>
I don't remember what monsters do that, but I know that there's a few that do, and they're in the regular monster set. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a></strong>: Those all need to be prevented in places where skipping random quests is normally prevented. 
</p>
